definition: to love/to be fond of/to like/affection/to be inclined (to do sth)/to tend to (happen)
silk/thread/trace/(cuisine) shreds or julienne strips/CL:條|条[tiao2]/classifier: a thread (of cloud, smoke etc), a bit, an iota, a hint (of sth) etc

sentences.english: Do you like this dress, Alice? Try it on.
sentences.chinese: 你喜歡這件洋裝嗎，愛莉絲？試穿看看嘛。

sentences.english: His children, Alice and Mike were very glad.
sentences.chinese: 他的兩個孩子，愛莉絲與麥可都非常的高興。

sentences.english: I can't get over the fact that Alice was promoted, and I wasn't.
sentences.chinese: 愛莉絲獲得升遷而我沒有，這件事我就是無法釋懷。

sentences.english: Other things being equal, Alice would marry Jim.
sentences.chinese: 如果其他條件都一樣的話，愛莉絲就會嫁給吉姆。

sentences.english: After lunch, Alice and Mike went for a walk in the woods.
sentences.chinese: 飯後，愛莉絲和麥可一起到林中去散步。
